pullRequest.body:
We show that the category of finite `G`-sets is a `PreGaloisCategory` and the forgetful functor to finite sets is a `FibreFunctor`.

I believe that the definitions should be in the `FintypeCat` namespace (not `PreGaloisCategory`).

This should be more friendly to the human reader:
```suggestion
    toFun := fun g y  Subtype.mk (Y. g y.val) <| by
```
This even makes the next line unnecessary :)

Does these lines deactivate the instances globally or only in a limited scope?
(I am sorry, I cannot review this PR more thoroughly right now... I shall come back to it later.)
I checked with `#synth` and they are only disabled in the scope of this section, so until the `end FintypeCat`.
I am not sure the definitions in this file need to be private.
I removed the `private` tag.
From this, it would be nice to extract a lemma `Finite.exists_mulEquiv` which would show the existence of a `mulEquiv` `G * G'` to a (finite) group `G'` in `Type`, and then use this lemma here.
See the latest commit, I moved it to `Mathlib.Logic.Equiv.TransferInstance`, thats what `#find_home` printed. I did not know how to name it, feel free to suggest something else.
Maybe `Finite.exists_type_zero_nonempty_mulEquiv`?
I moved this part into a new `namespace Finite` block with your suggested name.

The following syntax would be slightly more `mathlib` short-form style:
```suggestion
  letI := Equiv.group e.symm
  exact Fin n, inferInstance, inferInstance, MulEquiv.symm <| Equiv.mulEquiv e.symm
```

I would assume this is no longer necessary here.
```suggestion
```
The second one is indeed no longer necessary, the first one still is.
Sorry, I didn't realize this is a comment on the other file. Indeed, there they are no longer necessary and in the other file, the second one is not needed.

```suggestion
instance [Finite G] : HasColimitsOfShape (SingleObj G) FintypeCat.{w} := by
```
